-- EDF Agrees Life Extension for U.K. Plants, Mail on Sunday Says
-- B y   C l e m e n t i n e   F l e t c h e r
-- 2012-06-24T11:13:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-24/edf-agrees-life-extension-for-u-k-plants-mail-on-sunday-says.html
Electricite de France SA  agreed to
extend the life of seven of its nuclear power plants in the U.K.
by two years, according to the Mail on Sunday, which cited Chief
Executive Officer Vincent de Rivaz.  The plants will now be able to close in 2025 compared with
the previous 2023 deadline, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Clementine Fletcher in  London  
 cfletcher5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sara Marley at   smarley1@bloomberg.net  